verbs.description: dislodge (third-person singular simple present dislodges, present participle dislodging, simple past and past participle dislodged)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To remove or force out from a position or dwelling previously occupied.
(intransitive) To move or go from a dwelling or former position.
(transitive, figurative) To force out of a secure or settled position.
